# Why I'm Not Concerned About Overpopulation - Part One
## A History of Failed Predictions

>**_The Short Stuff:_** For decades, restrictionists have been saying that without large-scale, immediate cuts to immigration levels,
our country faces terrible effects of overpopulation. Even though their proposed solutions were entirely ignored, the doom they
predicted utterly failed to manifest.

# According to 'populationists', the United States has been overpopulated for most of a century.

